"tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/performance#bundle-size","content":"\\~101 B"},"273":{"id":"/docs/guides/performance-61","page_id":"/docs/guides/performance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/performance#bundle-size","content":"The CUID v2 entry point imports SHA3-512 from `@noble/hashes`, uniku's one runtime dependency; the size above excludes that external dependency's own weight."},"274":{"id":"/docs/guides/performance-62","page_id":"/docs/guides/performance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/performance#reproduce-these-numbers","content":"Run the benchmark and bundle-size tooling from the repository root:"},"275":{"id":"/docs/guides/performance-63","page_id":"/docs/guides/performance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/performance#reproduce-these-numbers","content":"`bench:summary` runs uniku's generators against the equivalent npm package and prints a comparison table. `bundle:summary` builds each entry point and reports its minified, gzipped size."},"276":{"id":"/docs","page_id":"/docs","type":"page","content":"Start here","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs"},"277":{"id":"/docs-0","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Pick an ID format for the job, then import only that generator."},"278":{"id":"/docs-1","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#the-library-contract","content":"The library contract"},"279":{"id":"/docs-2","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Install uniku once, then choose the identifier that fits the boundary in front of you: a database index, a public URL, or an API payload. Every generator has its own entry point, so a UUID, ULID, TypeID, Nanoid, CUID v2, KSUID, ObjectID, XID, or TSID only adds the strategy your application imports."},"280":{"id":"/docs-3","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Install uniku\" href=\"/docs/getting-started\" description=\"Generate your first 