from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","content":"Migration is usually an import change first. Keep the stored identifier format stable, then move generation behind the new direct entry point. Every example below shows the value returned by the uniku generator."},"298":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-11","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"uniku only generates UUID v4 and v7. There is no uniku equivalent for v1, v3, v5, or v6; keep the `uuid` package for those, or generate them elsewhere and only use uniku for v4 and v7 values."},"299":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-12","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"The rest of `uuid`'s API maps onto uniku's per-generator methods, scoped to the version you imported:"},"300":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-13","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuid`"},"301":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-14","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"uniku"},"302":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-15","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`parse(id)`"},"303":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-16","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuidv4.toBytes(id)` / `uuidv7.toBytes(id)`"},"304":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-17","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/f