ards, and tested end to end across Node.js, Bun, Deno, browsers, and Cloudflare Workers. The stability contract defines the entry points, validation boundaries, and runtime support policy that take effect with `uniku@1.0.0`."],[216,"The numbers below come from the repository's own benchmark and bundle-size tooling, including the rows where an npm alternative wins. Benchmarks run in CI on every push to `main` (GitHub Actions, `ubuntu-latest`), so they reflect ordinary Node.js execution rather than a tuned environment."],[331,"The package root is intentionally not exported. Import a generator or metadata module directly:"],[299,"The rest of `uuid`'s API maps onto uniku's per-generator methods, scoped to the version you imported:"],[329,"The stable direct imports exposed by uniku."],[94,"The type is auto-detected unless `--type` is given. For time-ordered IDs (UUID v7, ULID, TypeID, KSUID, ObjectID, XID, TSID), inspect extracts the embedded timestamp. Random-only IDs (UUID v4, CUID v2, Nanoid) report that no decodable metadata is available. Timestamp precision matches each generator: UUID v7, ULID, and TSID are millisecond-precision; KSUID, ObjectID, and XID are second-precision."],[116,"The usual shape"],[171,"This matters when an ID lives in a binary database column, a compact protocol payload, or a cache key. A UUID, for instance, is 16 bytes instead of its 36-character string form. The helpers also make the string boundary explicit: convert when data leaves your application, preserve bytes where the system already handles bytes."],[218,"This snapshot comes from the rolling `main` baseline updated on July 14, 2026. Treat the ratios as directional: shared-runner noise and dependency updates can move them. The live baseline is the current source of truth."],[360,"Thrown when"],[179,"Time order leaks creation time"],[178,"Time ordering is local"],[123,"Time-ordered formats also expose `timestamp()`. Each generator page lists its complete public API, including options, 